criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. 19 to 64 years of age, inclusive;

          2. Current and ongoing injection drug use with opioids OR hospitalized inpatients under
             the care of the St. Paul's Hospital Addiction Medicine Consult Team with current and
             ongoing use of high dose oral opioid medications;

          3. Current and past history of an opioid use disorder;

          4. Ability to communicate in English; and

          5. Ability to provide written informed consent and comply with study procedures.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Inability to understand study procedures due to changed health and/or mental status;

          2. Chest circumference greater than 115 cm;

          3. Women who are pregnant or breastfeeding

          4. Has a pacemaker or automatic cardioverter defibrillator (AICD) in situ;

          5. Diagnosed with atrial fibrillation;

          6. Have other medical devices (i.e. insulin pump) that precludes the use of the device;

          7. Allergies or skin conditions that preclude the use of adhesive electrodes; and

          8. Any other condition that, in the judgment of the investigator, presents a
             contraindication to study participation.
